quran[32]{c,v,t}:
  36,28,"And We did not send down against his people after him a host from heaven, nor do We send (such a thing)"
  36,29,It was only one shout and then they all were dead silent
  36,30,"Alas for the mankind! Whenever a Messenger came to them, they used to mock at him"
  36,31,Don’t they see how many generations We have destroyed before them who will not return to them
  36,32,"And surely, all of them will be brought before Us"
  36,33,And the dead land is a sign for them. We give it life and brings forth grain from it so that they eat from there
  36,34,"And We produces in it gardens of date-palms and grapes, and We cause springs of water to gush forth from it"
  36,35,so that they may eat the fruits thereof. Their hands did not make it. Should they not give thanks
  36,36,"Glory be to Him Who has created all things in pairs which the earth produces, as well as their own (human) kind, and other things which they don’t know"
  36,37,"And a sign for them is the night, when We withdraw the daylight from it, and behold, they are in darkness"
  36,38,"And the sun runs on its fixed course for a term (appointed) for it. That is the Decree of the All-Mighty, the All-Knower"
  36,39,"And the moon, We have measured its positions (phases) for it till it returns like the old dried curved date stalk"
  36,40,The sun is neither permitted to overtake the moon nor does the night outstrip the day. They all each float in its own orbit
  36,41,And a sign for them is that We carried their offspring in the laden ship (of Noah)
  36,42,And We have created for them similar (vessels) on which they ride
  36,43,"And if We will, We can drown them, and there will be no helper for them, nor will they be saved"
  36,44,except through the Mercy from Us and as an enjoyment for a while
  36,45,"And when it is said to them: “Beware of that which is before you (worldly punishments) and that which is behind you (punishments in the Hereafter) so that you may receive Mercy.”"
  36,46,"And whenever a sign of the Verses of their Lord comes to them, they turn away from it"
  36,47,"Whenever it is said to them:“Spend out of what Allah has provided you.” Those who disbelieve say to those who believe: “Should we feed those whom, if Allah wills, He (Himself) can feed? You are in plain error.”"
  36,48,"And they say: “When will this Promise (Resurrection) be fulfilled if you are truthful?”"
  36,49,"They are waiting for a single shout, which will seize them while they are disputing (among themselves)"
  36,50,"Then, they will neither be able to make a will, nor they will be able to return to their family"
  36,51,And the trumpet will be blown in and behold! They will come out quickly from the graves to their Lord
  36,52,"They will say: “Woe to us! Who has raised us up from our place of sleep?” (It will be said to them): “This is what the Gracious (Allah) had promised and the Messengers spoke the truth!”"
  36,53,"It will only be a single shout, so behold! They all will be brought up before Us"
  36,54,"This Day (of Resurrection), no soul will be wronged in anything and you will be rewarded for your deeds"
  36,55,"Surely, on that Day, the residents of the Paradise will be busy in joyful things"
  36,56,they and their wives will be in pleasant shade reclining on thrones
  36,57,They will have all kinds of fruits in it and they will get whatever they ask for
  36,58,"(it will be said to them): “Peace,” a Word from the Lord, Merciful"
  36,59,"(It will be said to sinners): “You get apart this Day, you criminals (from the believers)"